President Obama called President Karzai to discuss the tragic events in Benghazi, including the death of U.S. Embassy personnel. President Karzai expressed condolences and both leaders discussed the importance of working together to prevent similar violence from posing a threat to U.S. forces or Afghans. President Obama also reaffirmed his commitment to transferring detainees to Afghan authority while respecting Afghan sovereignty and protecting U.S. and Afghan forces. They agreed to speak again soon on other matters of mutual interest.